Each objection shall be in writing and contain:
The name and address of the objector;
A description of that portion of the land to which the objection applies, referenced to the description contained in the certificate of survey and accompanying plat;
The reasons for the objection;
All available documentary and factual information necessary to support the claim of the objector;
If the objection is made by a person claiming ownership under § 13-401(2) of this subtitle:
The name and current address of each person that has possessed the land under claim of ownership in the manner described in § 13-401 (2) of this subtitle;
The term of each possession; and
Any physical signs that accompanied each possession; and
If the objection is made by the State or any agency of the State claiming public use under § 13-401(3) of this subtitle:
A statement of the particular public purpose for which the land is required;
A description of a clear and compelling need for the land;
The anticipated date when the land will be used for the specified public purpose; and
A statement of whether the land adjoins any land already held by the objector.
